column5: Where are all pros doing shore fishing at port D? First time fishing at port dalhouse around the bridge and fall (lakeport RD), i only got some small SM, rock bass, and alot of gobies... There is no big fish at that spot?  I need some advise for port dalhousie. please  Thanks.
Use bigger baits, Gobie imitations might be good.
give it a few weeks then the salmon will be in there.....mostly just bass there right now
Thanks.... where is east wall at dalhousie?
Use the 5 inch "pink worm of death".
go to one of the piers and chuck a spoon or bounce a jig..  ya never know....
east peir you can access off ontario street...go past the subway restaurant and make a left at the next street...that street takes you down to the east side
